name: Titanium.XML.Comment
doc:
@platform android 0.8 @platform iphone 0.8 @platform ipad 0.8 @platform mobileweb 1.8 @editurl https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/edit/master/apidoc/Titanium/XML/Comment.yml

Represents the contents of an XML comment.

@description

Implements the DOM Level 2 API on Android and iOS with some non-standard extensions. Exposes the DOM Level 3 API implementation on Mobile Web.

property.name: apiName
property.doc:
The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.

@description

The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, Button returns Ti.UI.Button.

@platform android 3.2.0 @platform blackberry 3.2.0 @platform iphone 3.2.0 @platform ipad 3.2.0 @platform mobileweb 3.2.0
property.shortDoc: The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to. ...

property.name: attributes
property.doc:
A map of this node's attributes.

@description

As defined by the DOM specification, only Element nodes have attributes. For all other node types, this property is always null.
property.shortDoc: A map of this node's attributes. ...

property.name: bubbleParent
property.doc:
Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent.

@description

Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often established by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a click event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are table sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views to their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.

@platform android 3.0.0 @platform iphone 3.0.0 @platform ipad 3.0.0
property.shortDoc: Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent. ...

property.name: lifecycleContainer
property.doc:
The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.

@description

If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks will also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set to the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.

@platform android 3.6.0
property.shortDoc: The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy. ...

property.name: localName
property.doc:
Local part of the qualified name of this node.

@description

The local part of the qualified name that comes after the colon. That is, the name without the namespace prefix.
property.shortDoc: Local part of the qualified name of this node. ...

property.name: nodeName
property.doc:
Name of this node.

@description

Certain node types have constant values defined by the DOM specification:

  • Text node: text
  • Comment node: #comment
  • CDATA section node: #cdata-section
  • Document node: #document
  • Document fragment node: #document-fragment
property.shortDoc: Name of this node. ...

property.name: nodeType
property.doc: This node's type. One of ELEMENT_NODE, ATTRIBUTE_NODE, TEXT_NODE, CDATA_SECTION_NODE, ENTITY_REFERENCE_NODE, ENTITY_NODE, PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE, COMMENT_NODE, DOCUMENT_NODE, DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE, DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE, NOTATION_NODE.
property.shortDoc: This node's type. ...

property.name: nodeValue
property.doc:
Content (value) of this node.

@description

As defined in the DOM specification, the node value is always null for Document, DocumentFragment, DocumentType, Element, Entity, EntityReference, and Notation nodes.
property.shortDoc: Content (value) of this node. ...

property.name: ownerDocument
property.doc:
This node's owning document.

@description

Note that a node always has an owning document, even if it is not part of the document tree.

For more on node ownership, see ownerDocument issues in the W3C DOM FAQ.
property.shortDoc: This node's owning document. ...

property.name: parentNode
property.doc: This node's parent node.

property.name: prefix
property.doc:
Namespace prefix of this node.

@description

Read-only on iOS, read-write on other platforms.
property.shortDoc: Namespace prefix of this node. ...

property.name: previousSibling

property.name: text
property.doc: Content (value) of all text nodes within this node.
property.shortDoc: Content (value) of all text nodes within this node. ...

method.name: deleteData
method.doc: Remove a range of characters from the node. Upon success, data and length reflect the change. Throws an exception if this node is readonly, if offset is negative, offset is beyond the data's length, or if count is negative.

params.doc: The offset from which to start removing.

params.name: count
params.doc: The number of characters to delete. If the sum of offset and count exceeds length then all characters from offset to the end of the data are deleted.

method.name: removeEventListener
method.doc:
Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.

@description

Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the callback parameter is used to determine which listener to remove.

When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function in order to remove the listener later:

var listener = function() { Ti.API.info("Event listener called."); }
window.addEventListener('click', listener);

To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:

window.removeEventListener('click', listener);

params.name: callback
params.doc: Callback function to remove. Must be the same function passed to addEventListener.

method.shortDoc: Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...

@description

method.shortDoc: Replaces the node oldChild with the node newChild. ...

method.name: replaceData
method.doc: Replace the characters starting at the specified offset with the specified string. Throws an exception if this node is readonly, if offset is negative, offset is beyond the data's length, or if count is negative.

params.name: offset
params.doc: The offset from which to start replacing.

params.name: count
params.doc: The number of characters to replace. If the sum of offset and count exceeds length, then all characters to the end of the data are replaced; (i.e., the effect is the same as a remove method call with the same range, followed by an append method invocation).

params.name: arg
params.doc: The string with which the range must be replaced.

method.shortDoc: Replace the characters starting at the specified offset with the specified string. ...
